HSBC’s Preference to Stay in London, Talk of Change Speculative

-- B y   S t e p h e n   K i r k l a n d
-- 
2011-03-06T13:24:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-06/hsbc-prefers-to-keep-its-headquarters-based-in-london-chief-gulliver-says.html
  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  said the bank has
its “preference to remain headquartered” in  London  and the
reports of an “imminent change” is speculative, according to
an e-mailed statement by the company’s Chairman  Douglas Flint 
and Chief Executive Office Stuart Gulliver.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
